'''Alcaudete''' is a city located in the [[Province of Jaén (Spain)|province of Jaén]], [[Andalusia]], [[Spain]]. As of 2018, it has a population of 10,558. It is home to a 12th-14th century Moorish castle, located on the top of the hill commanding the town. Other sights include the ''Iglesia de Santa María la Mayor'' (15th century).
The city was established on the site of the Roman settlement of '''Sosontigi''', which was part of the ''[[Conventus iuridicus|Conventus]] [[Astigi]]tanus''.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ruiz Acevedo |first1=Juan |last2=de Paz Sánchez |first2=Manuel |editor1-last=Campos Carrasco |editor1-first=Juan M. |editor2-last=Bermejo Meléndez |editor2-first=Javier |title=Ciudades romanas de la provincia Baetica Vol. 1 |date=2018 |publisher=Servicio de Publicaciones de la Universidad de Huelva |location=Huelva, Spain |isbn=9788417776039 |page=82 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=GbKaDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA82 |language=es |chapter=Los límites de la Bética y las ciudades de los conventos astigitano e hispalense en las fuentes literarias grecolatinas}}</ref> The town of Fravasoson was 3 to 5 miles away.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Masdeu |first1=Juan Francisco |title=Historia critica de España, y de la cultura española: España romana. 1787-1807 |date=1789 |publisher=A. de Sancha |page=345 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=6hBXAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA345 |language=es}}</ref>
